    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a class containing around 950 living species of marine invertebrates having a globular or discoid form, and a rigid shell composed of many calcareous plates, in some species covered with projecting spines.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
